  "text": "In many real-world applications, fortunately, high-dimensional data are confined to locallylow-dimensional distributions-see Sect. 2. Hence, if we have a local regression technique that exploits these low-dimensional distributions, then, we can hope to carry over all the potential benefits of locally-weighted techniques to high-dimensional real-world data: locally-weighted regression requires inversion of the covariance matrix of the data, which is O(d [CITATION_1] , with d equal the dimensionality of the data. Thus, reducing the dimensionality is critical.",
